  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to see the constant list of added contacts or public chats so that I can switch between them any time.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: when entering new channel or contact to \"Join to public chat\" or \"Add new contact\" fields, then send a message in new chat - existing chat list is changing, and some chats are disappearing.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSent messages don't affect chat list\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nexisting chats are disappearing when the message is sent\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n\r\n- Install `status-desktop` \r\n- Open StatusIm \r\n- Create new account\r\n- Add one channel\r\n- Add second channel \r\n- Send a message to the second channel \r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: StatusIm desktop (version 2018-05-07)\r\n\r\n* Operating System: MacOS High Sierra 10.13.4, Ubuntu 18.04\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\nVideo: http://take.ms/oGw3T\r\n",
